    TargetOriginId: 'my-origin'

I see that you found a solution. The reason that cfn-flip don't work with anchors/aliases is because it's a transformation process to evaluate anchors and replace with metadata. The aws cloudformation package has this capability of getting anchors and some special tags and interpret them to pack and upload code to S3 for example.
I will evaluate the include this feature in a future release.", 'reactions': {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/awslabs/aws-cfn-template-flip/issues/comments/1091087839/reactions', 'total_count': 0, '+1': 0, '-1': 0, 'laugh': 0, 'hooray': 0, 'confused': 0, 'heart': 0, 'rocket': 0, 'eyes': 0}, 'performed_via_github_app': None}}
